a:5:{s:5:"title";s:71:"Bird Platform updates default permissions for Contacts and CRM access";s:16:"text-format-info";a:3:{s:10:"text-final";s:1044:"<p>Bird Platform updated its default permission model for Contacts and CRM data to reduce unnecessary access across workspaces.</p>
<h3>What changed</h3>
<p>Previously, Contacts and CRM access was included in base permissions for all users. Now, this access is not granted by default and requires a specific role.</p>
<h3>Who is affected</h3>
<p>Developer-only users: Contacts and CRM access is removed.</p>
<p>Marketing, Inbox, or CRM role users: No change; access continues.</p>
<h3>Why it matters</h3>
<p>This is a shift toward least-privilege access: users only see Contacts/CRM data if their assigned role requires it. In practice, some teams may see access-related friction until roles are updated.</p>
<h3>How to regain access</h3>
<p>If you need Contacts/CRM access but only have the Developer role, an Organization Admin must assign an additional role (Marketing, Inbox, or CRM) alongside Developer.</p>
<p>Read an original article: <a href="https://bird.com/en-us/updates">https://bird.com/en-us/updates</a></p>
